The paper proposes a new framework for goal-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on robotics applications, which suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is a likely category. The paper also discusses dynamic programming and optimization, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper applies the proposed framework to neural motion planning, which involves computer vision and image processing, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses policy gradient methodology, which is a common approach in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
